grade_evaluation.en:
- WRITTEN TESTS (pKT1, pKT2): cover themes passed in parasitology. Positive result (51-100%) gives up to 40% of the final result (each can give 20% or max 20 points, in sum max 40 points).
- EXAM: covers lectures and practicals on developmental biology and lectures on environment and evolutionary biology; these parts can give up to 60% of the final result (max 60 points).

Formation of final grade (sum total max points are 100):

- TESTS about materials passed in parasitology; can give max 40 points;

- EXAM, can give max 60 points, consists of:
1. environment and evolutionary biology, lectures; can give max 20 points;
2. developmental biology, lectures; can give max 20 points;
3. developmental biology, practicals; can give max 20 points.

0,4 x parasitology tests + 0,6 x EXAM [(0,2 x environment and evolutionary biology, lectures) + (0,2 x developmental biology, lectures) + (0,2 x developmental biology, practicals)]

